	<section>
		<header>
			<h1>Why I Decided to Continue Learning Programming</h1>
			<div class="itright">A Necessary Step!</div>
		</header>
		<p>Software engineering has evolved since I start working in
			software over 15 years ago. Enterprise applications are no longer
			exclusive to mid-size IBM-like corporations. The Open Source
			community has been busy developing servers and software frameworks
			that tests the old notions of adequacy in one knowing a single
			language and database running on an enterprise server. Nowadays even
			one with my experience would find it difficult to compete with
			younger engineers who know dozens of languages and who can create
			software covering the full spectrum of modern apps: server side,
			front end, web development, REST API, as well as device and IoT
			programming. I can no longer consider continuing my education a
			Bucket List choice. I must chose a Path that increases my technical
			skills else consider my career in programming all but over.</p>
	</section>

